BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10m6aGB5JVErPFO5aIztL
SUMMARY:Lushootseed Speaker Series: Natosha Gobin
DTSTAMP:20260307T070429Z
DTSTART:20260312T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP and join us for a special gathering as we welcome Natosha 
	Gobin \\(ɬalulic̓aʔ II\\)\, a Tulalip Tribal member and descendant of the 
	Snohomish\, Snoqualmie\, Sauk-Suiattle\, Skagit\, and Puyallup peoples. Na
	tosha's lineage connects her to the Gobin\, Young\, Price\, Hill\, Jones\,
	 and Williams families. She brings her connection to family into her roles
	 as a proud mother\, auntie\, and longtime community educator.\n\n \n\nFor
	 over 25 years\, Natosha has taught\, spoken\, and revitalized Northern Lu
	shootseed through the Tulalip Tribes Lushootseed Department\, where she no
	w serves as manager. Across her teaching journey\, she has worked with all
	 ages and currently co-teaches courses at Marysville-Pilchuck High School\
	, Northwest Indian College\, and the University of Washington.\n\n \n\nOpe
	n to the public at no cost\, this event offers an opportunity to hear stor
	ytelling rooted in Natosha’s ancestral background and extensive knowledge 
	of the Northern Lushootseed language. Early registration is encouraged\, a
	s space and tickets are limited.\n\n \n\nCo-sponsored with the Lemieux Lib
	rary & McGoldrick Learning Center.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/
	#/details/lushootseed-speaker-series-natosha-gobin/18260239/2026-03-12T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/lushootseed-speaker-serie
	s-natosha-gobin/18260239/2026-03-12T00
LOCATION:Lemieux Library\, Byte Cafe\, Second Floor\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
